individual_records.phenotype_details: axonal sensory-motor polyneuropathy, mild hypertrophic cardiomyopathy
individual_records.evidence_sentence: Sequence analysis of TTR gene confirmed the presence of the F64L (p. Phe84Leu) variant.

functional_data.summary: The variant is associated with hereditary transthyretin amyloidosis.

variants.additional_notes: The patient had a history of carpal tunnel syndrome and showed signs consistent with amyloid deposits.
key_quotes: Sequence analysis of TTR gene confirmed the presence of the F64L (p. Phe84Leu) variant.
The MR findings are consistent with the amyloid deposits between the fascicles of the sciatic nerve, supporting the clinical diagnosis.

extraction_metadata.notes: The extraction was straightforward as the relevant variant was clearly mentioned in the clinical vignette.
